Johannesburg - Violent clashes between two taxi
associations occurred in Marapong, near Lephalale on Thursday, Limpopo police
said. "This morning we received a call from the community
to say somebody was being assaulted in Marapong," said police spokesperson
Frans Mokoena. "The conflict was between the local taxi association
and the recent, newly formed metered taxi [group]." A driver of the local taxi association was assaulted and
his taxi damaged. Seven of the metered taxis were burnt, as well as a house
and two shops. Two people of each organisation had been arrested,
Mokoena said. The injured driver was taken to hospital.